How transparency, sustainibility and trust are represented on the TEC?
trust, transparency, sustainability
How are these values - transparency, sustainability and trust-  represented or embodied in the TEC community?

Transparency = Is one of the values that is embodied on a WG but also has been built in and growth in the entire community. It's one of the easiest to exemplify and the easiest to empower an individiual since it has very low knowledge barrier

Trust = is a value that has / is grown in the community, through many workstreams such as soft gov, communitas and gravity, and we just recently, a few months ago, changed the idea of conflict resolution (reactive) towards trust creation as a method to avoid conflict. Trust has been built also with open processes and providing accesbility to these processes.

Sustainibility = we didn't think about it very well. We were focused more on the sustainibility of our "processes" and frameworks and not so much on the economic sustanbility of the organization, it came as more transversal value recently, since 3 or 4 months ago, were we embrace the conversation about token utility and the sustainable future

transparency: auditability of spending, group discussions & decision making

trust: starting from trusted seed as initial condition

sustainability: unsure if TEC has achieved this yet

Sustainibility = Through SampoWG looking and researching about different ways to find utility of a token
Partnering with other organizations, like Aragon or Token Academy, to bring forms of revenue to the TEC
Sustanibility through the parameters setting of the token, like token freeze.
Gravity is trying to be sustainable by offering services to other communities and iterating in the TEC frameworks to launching a token economy in the future
There is a invisible sustainibility layer, provided by our cultural and social reinforcements: keeping onboarding calls available, providing time for everyone who seeks to partner with us, and so on.
Or even things that create "sense of belonging" that helps the long term sustainability like: NFT to hatchers, or SWAG
short-term: token-gating  the knowledge resources that we create for the commons thereby sacrificing the radically open source value - little by little
e.g. we could create an open source library, or we can say you need $TEC to access it - thereby creating utility for the token and sacrificing radical open source
^^ more courageous research on "abundance economy" that @liviade mentioned in the beginning can also be a parallel path / branches of evolutionary search of design space

Trust = built through main layers of governance, cultural/social, and economic one. Our governance is for anyone to engage, and how to access it. Cultural/Social = we try to always be supportive of anyone who joins our community. Economic = on the design of the token, and other iniatives
